			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				I feel the same way.  The exact same thing happened on Hib Pellinor.  At 35+ it's almost impossible to get a group, regardless of what class that you're playing, unless you're part of the PL mafia.   <br>  <br> Not only is it annoying and all those things you say, but it's also seemed to have ruined realm spirit somewhat - and to me this is by far the best part about DaoC, and what separates it from other games.  Most of the time when you send a polite request ; (hey - would your group have room for a druid?) you are ignored completely.  The silence is deafening.   <br>  <br> The worst thing that I've found is that it even carries over into RvR. Communication is terrible out there and we are constantly getting beaten down because of it (at least that's part of the reason <img src="http://media.ign.com/boardfaces/1.gif" border="0" alt="happy" hspace="0" vspace="0">  ). <br>  <br> Anyway, this is not a diatribe.  I've rolled up an Infil and am having fun with it, but I don't really plan on heading back to Hib, unless something dramatic happens over there. <br>  <br> 
