		<tr valign=top>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				focus pull is no where near the fastest way to lvl, the focus spells dmg leeches exp from the group members.... <br>  <br>  <br> Hate to say it but no...the Focus DS leeched NO xp from the mobs your fighting. This is just one of the continuous myths of how pets suck xp. Is also why lots of people use this method of pulling...xp is sick, with just an enchanter and 3 healers you can go pull hulks or knights in DF, have even done some galla' trash mobs with focus pull. Add a Menty or have a bard w/ Pow 5 your looking at next to no downtime. Xp drained by your pet only happens if you pet actually lands a hit on the mob. Since most the stuff your pulling is deep purple to the pet, he doesn't hit and doesn't drain xp. I believe the FDS damage is calculated as if you did the damage not the pet...if the DS is actually managing to drain xp somehow, it comes no where near the amount of xp 4 more group memembers will drain.  <br>  <br> I personally hate focus pull groups, hell me and 2 druids focus pulled the mid prince the other day. Boring as hell those grps are, and I have to agree with Mclogan, it overall makes lvling in the realm a pain for newcomers. Tanks have virtually no place in xp groups anymore.
