		<tr valign=top>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				While I am currently levelling a druid and benefiting from focus pull groups, I think they are bad for the realm and the game. <br>  <br> While old-style groups (pbae groups, or mez groups) did exclude certain classes (stalkers mainly) they did require a much wider mix of characters and were less likely to tolerate several afk people being PLed.  <br>  <br> Typical 40s hib group now seems to be 3 chanters, 3 healers and 2 afk shades. Typical waiting time for a tank in these groups is measured in days not hours. <br> This is especially bad in hibernia as we have the two core skills needed (PBAE and focus DS) in one character which is also one of the best in RvR.  <br>  <br> The ability of FDS to take out very high level mobs (Galladoria, Tuscan etc) is also unbalanced IMHO. I would suggest a nerfing of FDS is long overdue - either directly (e.g., change aggro rule so pet triggers BAF as a normal group member) or indirectly, move all FDSes to the pet line for chanters (and cabalists) - though this would just benefit those people with the resources to have a separate enchantments chanter for PvE.
						<p><span class="SignatureTitle">-----signature-----</span>
						<div class="SignatureText">
						Shika, 50 lurikeen shield heroine of Guinevere <br> 
						</div>
							

